title: Tour guide
author: fellowship9
pages:
#- A tour guide to the city of Datan-Kegeth.

To begin your tour please make sure you are standing in the main entrance.


As you first enter the main hall pause for a second to take in the sheer size of the 
#- place, as well as the attention to detail. This shows most obviously in the faces carved onto the central pillar as well as the perfectly symetrical structure of the pillars.

From here please turn right and go down the stair case
#- To your left is the entrance to the Copperwood district. We will return here shortly. Go down the stairs to your right. 

You are now at the bottom layer of the main hall. In front of you is the cities notice board.
#- To your right, in the south-east corner, are the storage room and agricultural farms. In the north-east are the animal pens and sheep jail.

In the north-west corner are the Datan-kegeth branch of the world-famous
#- Prussian publishing co. and the subway station for the rail leading to Carbon. If you wish to do so go there now and return here to continue the tour.

In the south-west the only room of any significance if the hilariously named 'mush-room'.
#- To visit the source of the holds legendary wealth procede to the north side of the central pillar where you will find the entrance to the iron farm. If you gain access be sure to pause for a moment of silent reflection infront of the tomb of Horatio.
#- After you are done there go up the northern stairs and straight ahead to enter the market district (under construction) where a weary traveller can rest and buy suppplies.

The other three sides of the central layer  
#- are occupied by the 3 housing districts, Copperwood, silverstone and ebonbrick. Feel free to marvel at the architecture, especially in the public squares, but refrain from entering private rooms.
#- For the next part of the tour please find your way to the western door of the top layer. 

This is the entrance to the archery range and arena (under construction) where the representatives of ations gather to compete.
#- To the Noth lies the entrance to the Palace of the Triumvirate, where the three lords dwell. Unfortunately access is denied to commoners, but throught the door you may glimpse the lavish building style and elegant carpets.
#- This concludes our tour. thank you very much for taking the time to visit Datan-Kegeth. If you wish to join the city please contact a lord
#- 